adjectives.description: reputed (comparative more reputed, superlative most reputed)

examples: He was good to look on, brawly dressed, and with a tongue in his head that would have wiled the bird from the tree. Moreover, he was of gentle kin, and she was a poor lass biding in a cot house with an ill-reputed mother.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of repute
